<ext_descriptions module_directory="extended_task_element" schema_file="arm.xml" describe.selects="YES" describe.subtype_constraints="YES" rcs.date="$Date: 2006/03/14 14:51:38 $" rcs.revision="$Revision: 1.2 $">
<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  Schema: Extended_task_element_arm
   <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Extended_task_element_arm">
</ext_description><!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Extended_task_element_arm  Entity: Decision_path  
   <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Decision_path"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Extended_task_element_arm.Decision_path">
A <b>Decision_path</b> is a component of a <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Multiple_decision_point"/> that identifies the <express_ref linkend="condition:arm:Condition_arm.Condition"/> associated with a particular path from the decision point and the <express_ref linkend="task_element:arm:Task_element_arm.Task_element"/> to be executed if the condition is TRUE.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Extended_task_element_arm  Entity: Decision_path  Attribute: condition 
   <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Decision_path.condition"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Extended_task_element_arm.Decision_path.condition">
the <express_ref linkend="condition:arm:Condition_arm.Condition"/> to be evaluated to TRUE for this <b>Decision_path</b> to be executed.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Extended_task_element_arm  Entity: Decision_path  Attribute: defined_in 
   <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Decision_path.defined_in"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Extended_task_element_arm.Decision_path.defined_in">
the <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Multiple_decision_point"/> for which this <b> Decision_path</b> has been defined.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Extended_task_element_arm  Entity: Decision_path  Attribute: path_element 
   <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Decision_path.path_element"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Extended_task_element_arm.Decision_path.path_element">
the <express_ref linkend="task_element:arm:Task_element_arm.Task_element"/> to be executed if the <b>condition</b> is TRUE.
</ext_description><!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Extended_task_element_arm  Entity: Multiple_decision_point  
   <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Multiple_decision_point"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Extended_task_element_arm.Multiple_decision_point">
A <b>Multiple_decision_point</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="task_element:arm:Task_element_arm.Structured_task_element"/>.
It identifies a number of alternative <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Decision_path"/> of which only one may be taken based on the conditions associated with these paths.
If the conditions associated with more than one <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Decision_path"/> are true then it is undefined which of these decision paths is executed. Similarly, if no condition is satisfied, the execution path is undefined.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Extended_task_element_arm  Entity: Multiple_decision_point  Attribute: paths 
   <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Multiple_decision_point.paths"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Extended_task_element_arm.Multiple_decision_point.paths">
the collection of possible <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Decision_path"/> associated with this decision point.
</ext_description><!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Extended_task_element_arm  Entity: Task_io  
   <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Task_io"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Extended_task_element_arm.Task_io">
A <b>Task_io</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="task_element:arm:Task_element_arm.Task_element_assignment" /> that identifies that the assigned <express_ref linkend="task_element:arm:Task_element_arm.task_item"/> is either an input or an output from this <express_ref linkend="task_element:arm:Task_element_arm.Task_step"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Extended_task_element_arm  Entity: Task_io  Attribute: assigned_task_element 
   <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Task_io.assigned_task_element"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Extended_task_element_arm.Task_io.assigned_task_element">
the <express_ref linkend="task_element:arm:Task_element_arm.Task_step"/> for which the input or out put is assigned.
</ext_description><!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Extended_task_element_arm  Entity: Task_io_hierarchy  
   <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Task_io_hierarchy"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Extended_task_element_arm.Task_io_hierarchy">
A <b>Task_io_hierarchy</b> is a relationship between two <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Task_io"/> that asserts that the <b>parent</b> task io is represented by the <b>child</b> task io at the next level of breakdown.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Extended_task_element_arm  Entity: Task_io_hierarchy  Attribute: child 
   <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Task_io_hierarchy.child"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Extended_task_element_arm.Task_io_hierarchy.child">
the <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Task_io"/> that represents the input or output specified in the <b>parent</b> at the next level of breakdown.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Extended_task_element_arm  Entity: Task_io_hierarchy  Attribute: parent 
   <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Task_io_hierarchy.parent"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Extended_task_element_arm.Task_io_hierarchy.parent">
the <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Task_io"/> which is represented by the <b>child</b> at the next level of task step breakdown.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Extended_task_element_arm  Entity: Task_io_hierarchy  Where: wr1 
   <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Task_io_hierarchy.wr:wr1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Extended_task_element_arm.Task_io_hierarchy.wr:wr1">
Ensure the parent and child relationships are for the same role.
</ext_description><!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Extended_task_element_arm  Entity: Task_step_hierarchy  
   <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Task_step_hierarchy"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Extended_task_element_arm.Task_step_hierarchy">
A <b>Task_step_hierarchy</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="task_element:arm:Task_element_arm.Task_element_relationship"/> that represents the fact that a <b>parent</b> is broken down into a lower level <b>child</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Extended_task_element_arm  Entity: Task_step_hierarchy  Attribute: child 
   <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Task_step_hierarchy.child"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Extended_task_element_arm.Task_step_hierarchy.child">
the <express_ref linkend="task_element:arm:Task_element_arm.Task_step"/> which represents a lower level breakdown component of the <b>parent</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Extended_task_element_arm  Entity: Task_step_hierarchy  Attribute: parent 
   <express_ref linkend="extended_task_element:arm:Extended_task_element_arm.Task_step_hierarchy.parent"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Extended_task_element_arm.Task_step_hierarchy.parent">
the <express_ref linkend="task_element:arm:Task_element_arm.Task_step"/> which represents a higher level composition of the <b>child</b> along with other children represented by other, similar relationships to the same <b>parent</b>.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
